Subject: Re: [T2] AL75X alternator rebuilt by Bosch

On 3/2/05 12:02 AM, "Chuck Shultz" <chuxbus(-at-)earthlink.net> wrote:

> So... the AL75X I got doesn't have the same "shell" as the original.
> It doesn't have a provision for the cooling boot from the fan shroud.
> Should I not even bother installing it and set out on a quest for the
> proper equipment, or is the "new" shell an improved and acceptable
> replacement?

I think you need the sheet metal cover for the rear of the assembly. The
AL75 cooling boot is attached to the sheet metal cover, not the alternator
itself. The cover is not supplied with a rebuilt alternator, you re-use your
old one.


